There are three concepts of note:
Blame
Responsibility
Ability
I do not find that Blame is a useful metric when solving problems with regards to real life human people. While the human driver is more Responsible for the accident than the company (as far as I can tell, level 2 automation is approximately the level at which modern non-stick shift cars operate), the company is very likely to be more Able to resolve the financial fallout from the accident than the driver, who is a single person. Therefore, it will be more useful for the victim involved if Aeon takes on liability for the accident.
